President Biden and Prime Minister Modi held a meeting in the Oval Office, where they discussed strengthening the partnership between India and the United States. They highlighted the progress made in various areas, such as defense, economics, space, and clean energy. Both leaders emphasized the importance of democracy, human rights, freedom, and the rule of law. Prime Minister Modi expressed gratitude for President Biden's commitment to India and the warm reception given to him and his delegation. They acknowledged the significance of the India-U.S. relationship in promoting global peace and stability. The leaders also mentioned the strong people-to-people ties between the two countries. The press asked some unrelated questions regarding President Biden's previous remarks about Chinese President Xi Jinping and the well-being of Hunter Biden.